cs.CV, cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.MM, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper proposes an intraoperative component planning system based on two C-arm x-ray images that are combined with 3-D augmented reality (AR) visualization. Computer vision techniques are used to overlay the RGBD data onto the real-time images. 
2. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper proposes an easy-to-use system that simplifies impactor and cup placement according to the planning by providing a real-time RGBD data overlay. The system is evaluated in a user study comprising four orthopedic surgeons. 
3. cs.RO (Robotics): Although the paper does not explicitly mention robotics, the use of AR visualization and computer vision techniques in the proposed system can be related to robotics. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper uses RGBD data overlay to provide real-time visualization during the surgery. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics): The paper uses 3-D augmented reality (AR) visualization to simplify impactor and cup placement according to the planning.
